Your sponsor will also be responsible for you. You can find who is on at any one time by typing the command &lt;/who all random&gt; <br>(Note: Guild members can sponsor more than one fledgling.)<br><br>5. Perform Fledgling Quest or Community Service quest<br>Details of the quest can be found at www.eqrandomacts.com and you can perform either one with the assistance and advice of your sponsor.<br><br>6. Guild Tagging <br>Upon successful completion of your Quest, your sponsor must notify Meriel Silvertree or Gwion Llwellyn either by posting here on the board, or through a tell in game, you will then receive your Random Acts Tag at the next scheduled First Aid Camp (FA).<br>First Aid Camps are generally held every two weeks, the first one on a Saturday, and the next one on a Sunday.<br><br>7. Probationary Membership<br>Probationary Membership will last until you attend the *next* regularly scheduled FA and barring any difficulties you will be accepted into the guild as a full member.<br><br>8. Alternate Characters<br>You will be able to have one alternate character tagged every two weeks.<br><br>The road is long Fledgling, but you will find assistance, advice and kindness upon the way. <br><br>If you have any difficulties you may contact me at morgyra@aol.com or the council at eqrandomacts@hotmail.com<br><br>Be proactive and seek out guild members near you both in Norrath and here upon the boards. <br><br>For our records it would be helpful if you could provide us with details of your name, class, race, level, playing times, and e-mail address if you have not yet done so. <br><br>Safe journeys to you,  <br><br>Morgaina Oakenshield<br>Proud Member of Random Acts<br> <p><br><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.jsp?num=723"><img src="http://morgaina.no-frills.net/images/morgbackTN.jpg"></a><center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http